Mission.Author: KingRaptor
Mission.Description: On this lonely frontier world, a rogue excavation team makes an unexpected discovery that will alter the history of the galaxy.
Mission.DescriptionStory:
It is the turn of a new millenium. Humanity is dead.
For countless years, we fought amidst the stars. For power, for resources, for causes. It to this end that the Machine was first made. To forge our weapons, to bleed and die for us.
It was these wars that proved to be our eventual undoing. One way or another, we all died out, leaving our machine successors to pick up the pieces.
And yet the wars remain. Huge robot armies struggle for control of the galaxy, each in service of their factions. In this they are led by the powerful Commanders, all-capable machines of war, relics from the days of Man. Split along ideological lines, they continue to tear the galaxy asunder in their conflicts inherited from their long-gone masters.
But small perturbations can have impacts far beyond the magnitude of the original force.
[img]http://licho.eu/alba/SunriseCampaign/lilith_beautyshot_cartoon.sized.jpg[/img]
Her name was Lilith, leader of an independent exploration team. She travelled the lonely systems of the frontier, far from the core worlds, digging up pre-collapse relics on behalf of the major factions. In one such system, on a seemingly unassuming planet orbiting an unremarkable G2 primary, she made what would prove to be the greatest discovery of all. One that would bring an end to millenia of conflict, and perhaps restore that which was lost for so long.
Mission.Name: Sunrise Pilot Episode (beta v0.35)

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Looks like they've gotten here before us, and dug in deep. Do we withdraw?
I did not come all the way here to see a bunch of buzzards steal my prize. Lancers, get ready to fight!

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: A Radar Tower over there would give us a heads-up on what we're going into.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: A Radar Tower would be useful for identifiying enemy concentrations from a distance. Build one on the designated location.
TriggerLogic.Title: Build Radar Tower

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Radar indicates the position of nearby enemy units as "dots" or "blips". The position of the dots "wavers" around the unit's true position, so long-range precision weapons are unlikely to hit. Additionally, radar cannot see through terrain, and radar-stealthed/jammed or cloaked units can go undetected by radar.
The Radar Tower also has good visual sight distance in addition to its radar, which can be useful for getting more line-of-sight coverage.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: The Athena special operations constructor is carrying your AI core. Do not let it be destroyed, whatever the cost!
TriggerLogic.Title: Protect Athena

TriggerLogic.Description: You've arrived at an excavation site for rumored prewar artifacts, but a bunch of pirates have gotten here first. Fight through them and get to the bottom of the crater where the artifacts are housed.
TriggerLogic.Title: Secure Dig Site

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Okay, it seems the north entrance to the crater is more heavily fortified than I'd like to deal with. We'll loop around the southwest and punch through their perimeter.
A number of storage bunkers are scattered around the excavation site. Some of them might still contain usable equipment.
Assault unit, Zeus class. Few better friends in a straight up fight.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Bunker 1") Spring.TransferUnit(unitID, 0, false) Spring.SetUnitNeutral(unitID, true)

TriggerLogic.Message: A Firewalker, huh. I guess some bots just wanna watch the world burn.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Bunker 2") Spring.TransferUnit(unitID, 0, false) Spring.SetUnitNeutral(unitID, true)

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: It could be useful for knocking out those defenses from a safe distance.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Bunker 3") Spring.TransferUnit(unitID, 0, false) Spring.SetUnitNeutral(unitID, true)
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Roach") for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.SetUnitCloak(unitID, true) end

TriggerLogic.Message: Roaches! Just one of these seeded in the path of an assault group can really ruin its day. I think we can make good use of these.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Crawling bombs like the Roach are designed to get close and explode, inflicting heavy damage on anyone in the vicinity. They should be spaced out to prevent chain explosions.
The Roach can burrow to avoid detection until enemies are close, then jump them and blow up. It should not attempt to charge enemy units with accurate weapons.
Incredible... a Crabe! Get it hunkered down somewhere it can put its firepower and armor to best use.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Bunker 4") Spring.TransferUnit(unitID, 0, false) Spring.SetUnitNeutral(unitID, true)

TriggerLogic.Message: Alright, get that tech lab secured and get me whatever they were digging out. Make it snappy, we don't want to be here when they get off their asses and try to retake it.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: You've secured the dig site, now hold it until we can recover the artifacts we need.
TriggerLogic.Title: Defend Dig Site

TriggerLogic.Message: Chief, long range sensors are picking up a lot of reentry signatures. We're going to have a a real fight on our hands shortly.
Defensive positions around the lab! I'll deploy constructors and more units to cover us. And get the remaining bunkers!

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The LLT is your basic defense. Armed with a continuous-fire beamlaser, it is cheap and works reasonably well against most targets, particularly raiders. Long-ranged skirmishers and artillery units can hit it with impunity from outside its range, however, while assault units can tank its damage and punch through - or destroy - an LLT line.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Alright, I think I've found what they were looking for. It's... Homo Magnus! It's... it's...
What is it? Speak clearly and report!
It's an organic stasis chamber, ma'am! Readouts indicate a live human is inside!
What?! Do an external scan!
Twice already, ma'am! And there's something else here too... a functional commander unit!
...Damn. This is getting bigger than we're equipped to deal with. Alright, now we really need to get out of here. Roc! How soon can you reach us?
Gunning the engines as hard as I can, ma'am! ETA ten... no, eight minutes!
Do it in five!
Y-Yes, ma'am!

The Defender missile turret is the other "basic" defense. This cheap, fragile turret fires three missiles in a quick volley, after which it must spend some time reloading. Its range and upfront damage make it quite effective as a deterrent against skirmishers and aircraft, but anything with a decent amount of HP will simply absorb the damage and smash it.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Boss, I'm picking up incoming gunships. We should get some anti-air defenses soon.

The cheapest of the "true" anti-air fixed defenses, the Razor's Kiss has a rapid-fire weapon that does well against gunships, although it has trouble hitting fast-moving planes. When no firing, the Razor's Kiss "pops down" into its hardened shell, taking only 25% damage from enemy fire.
